                <h5> 2. COOKIE POLICY </h5>
                    <p> Effective Date: 20 May 2026 </p>

                 <h6> 2.1 Introduction </h6>
                    <p> 
                        This Cookie Policy explains how Emus Institute uses cookies and similar technologies on emusinstitute.com and associated online learning systems.
                    </p>
                     
                 <h6> 2.2 What Are Cookies? </h6>

                    <p> 
                        Cookies are small text files stored on a user’s device when visiting a website. Cookies help websites function efficiently and improve user experience.
                    </p>
                 <h6> 2.3 Types of Cookies We Use </h6>
                    <p> <i> A. Essential Cookies </i></p>
                    <p> These cookies are necessary for: </p>
                        <ul> 
                            <li>  Website functionality</li>
                            <li> User authentication</li>
                            <li>  Security features</li>
                            <li> Session management</li>
                            <li>  Course access</li>
                        </ul>
                    <p> Without these cookies, certain services may not function properly. </p>

                    <p> <i> B. Performance and Analytics Cookies </i></p>
                    <p> These cookies help us understand: </p>
                        <ul> 
                            <li>  Website traffic</li>
                            <li>  User behavior</li>
                            <li>  System performance</li>
                            <li>  Learning platform usage</li>
                        </ul>
                    <p> Analytics information may be aggregated and anonymized. </p>
                    <p><i> C. Functional Cookies </i></p>
                    <p> These cookies remember: </p>
                        <ul> 
                               <li> User preferences</li>
                               <li> Language settings</li>
                               <li>  Login details</li>
                               <li> Accessibility preferences</li>
                        </ul>
                    <p> D. Marketing Cookies </p>
                    <p> Where permitted, marketing cookies may be used to: </p>
                        <ul> 
                            <li>Deliver promotional content </li>
                            <li>  Measure advertising effectiveness</li>
                            <li>Personalize communications </li>
                        </ul>
                    
                    <h6> 2.4 Third-Party Cookies </h6>
                    <p> Third-party service providers may place cookies on our systems, including: </p>
                        <ul> 
                            <li> Analytics providers</li>
                            <li> Payment gateways</li>
                            <li> Video hosting platforms</li>
                            <li> Learning technology providers</li>
                            <li> Social media integrations</li>
                        </ul>
                    
                    <p> 2.5 Managing Cookies </p>
                    <p> Users may control cookies through browser settings. </p>
                    <p> Most browsers allow users to: </p>
                        <ul> 
                            <li> Delete cookies</li>
                            <li> Block cookies</li>
                            <li> Restrict tracking technologies</li>
                            <li> Receive cookie notifications</li>
                        </ul>

                    <p> Disabling cookies may affect the functionality of some services. </p>
                    <h6> 2.6 Consent </h6>
                    <p> 
                        By continuing to use emusinstitute.com, users consent to the use of cookies as described in this policy unless they disable cookies through browser settings.
